      "amount": "1/4 cup",
      "notes": "or to taste"
    },
    {
      "name": "Vegetable broth",
      "amount": "4 cups",
      "notes": "homemade or store-bought"
    },
    {
      "name": "Hot sauce (optional)",
      "amount": "1-2 teaspoons",
      "notes": "for added heat"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a large hot pot over medium-high heat.",
    "Add the onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened and lightly browned (5-7 minutes).",
    "Add the carrots and cook, stirring occasionally, until they begin to soften (3-5 minutes).",
    "Add the Brussels sprouts, salt, cumin, black pepper, and garlic powder. Stir to combine.",
    "Pour in the vegetable broth and bring the mixture to a boil.",
    "Reduce the heat to medium-low, cover, and simmer, stirring occasionally, until the vegetables are tender and the liquid has been absorbed (15-20 minutes).",
    "Stir in the chopped cilantro (if using) and hot sauce (if using).",
    "Serve hot, garnished with additional cilantro if desired."
  ],
